    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1967-05-26T10:10:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1967-05-26T10:10:00-05:00" n="70"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d70">
                <head>70. Memorandum From the President’s Special Assistant (<persName
                        corresp="#p_RWW1" type="from">Rostow</persName>) to President <persName
                        corresp="#p_JLB1" type="to">Johnson</persName>
                    <note n="1" type="source" xml:id="d70fn1">Source: <persName corresp="#p_JLB1"
                            >Johnson</persName> Library, National Security File, Country File,
                        Middle East Crisis, Vol. II. Top Secret; [<hi rend="italic">codeword not
                            declassified</hi>].</note>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>Washington</placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian"
                            when="1967-05-26T11:10:00-04:00">May 26, 1967, 11:10 a.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p rend="flushleft">Mr. President:</p>
                <p>Herewith our Military Attachés in Tel Aviv state their belief that “Israel is
                    approaching a decision in favor of a preemptive attack”; and they explain
                        why.<note n="2" xml:id="d70fn2">The attachment conveying this assessment was
                        telegram STRIKE 4553 from <gloss target="#t_CINCSTRIKE1">CINCSTRIKE</gloss>,
                        May 26, 0801Z.</note>
                </p>
                <p>[<hi rend="italic">2½ lines of source text not declassified</hi>]<note n="3"
                        xml:id="d70fn3">[<hi rend="italic">text not declassified</hi>]</note>
                </p>
                <p>One underlying problem is, of course, that the Israelis feel that the longer a
                    confrontation over Aqaba is avoided—and the issue is kicked around in the <gloss
                        target="#t_UN1">UN</gloss>—the more their rights in the Straits will become
                    eroded.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="#p_RWW1">Walt</persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
